abstract.label: Abstract
abstract.value: The collection contains the papers documenting the political career and private interests of Federalist statesman Rufus King. The collection includes official and private correspondence with other political figures in the early history of the United States, letterbooks, account books, notebooks, financial documents, diaries, memoranda, and essays.

p.value: Photocopying undertaken by staff only. Limited to twenty exposures of stable, unbound material per day. (Researchers may not accrue unused copy amounts from previous days.) Researchers on site may print out unlimited copies from microfilm reader-printer machines at per-exposure rates. See guidelines in Reading Room for details.
This collection should be cited as the Rufus King Papers, The New-York Historical Society.

Ernst, Robert, 
                <title render="italic" type="simple">Rufus King: American Federalist</title>. Chapel Hill: University of North Carolina Press, 1968.
This collection supports research on the nuances of King's lengthy political career as well as the early political history of the United States.
